name: Dave: Zombie Hunter
description:
DAVE: ZOMBIE HUNTER
Written by Stewart Cook
Art by Rob O' Connor and Tim Ide
80pages
Mature Readers
THE COMPLETE STORY - AT LAST! The zombie apocalypse is here and there's only one man who can stop it, DAVE, DAVE: ZOMBIE HUNTER! Along with his girlfriend Vera, his best mate Chuck and the irrepressible 1960's pop phenomenon The Monty's, Dave must save the world from zombies, gas station scams and traffic violations! 

Includes bonus art gallery featuring pieces by Joel van der Knaap, Dave Heinrich, Dean Rankine, Jason Steen, Kara Gillett, Wolf Reynolds and Stewart Cook. Also includes the full script for Operation: Gehanna and a sketch gallery including character design work by Rob O'Connor.

name: Home Made #1
description:
64 pages. 

Home Made is a quarterly anthology of genre works by some of Australia's finest graphic novelists. 

Issue #1 features:
Thindon - Written and drawn by Tim Ide (Fantasy)
Rewired - Written and drawn by Joel van der Knaap (Sci-Fi)
Killerroo - Written by Darren Close with art by  Gee Hale (Superhero)
Alone In The Rain Again - Written by Daren White with art by Jason Paulos (Superhero/Drama)
The Nexus Point - Written by Stewart Cook with art by Robert Hall (Superhero)
Meat - by Ben Michael Byrne (Sci-Fi)
Todesengel (ongoing) - Written and draw by Stewart Cook (War/Superhero)

Issue #1 features a cover by internationally renowned artist Molly Crabapple

Thindon, Rewired, Killerroo, The Nexus Point and Todesengel are all ongoing stories, so don't miss out on the first chapter of each tale!

*Please note orders will ship from July 2012*
